Events.html: 1736 – Stanislaus I of Poland abdicates his throne.

Events.html: 1788 – The British First Fleet, led by Arthur Phillip, sails into Port Jackson (Sydney Harbour) to establish Sydney, the first permanent European settlement on the continent. Commemorated as Australia Day.

Events.html: 1808 – Rum Rebellion, the only successful (albeit short-lived) armed takeover of the government in Australia.

Events.html: 1841 – The United Kingdom formally occupies Hong Kong, which China later formally cedes.

Events.html: 1855 – Point No Point Treaty is signed in Washington Territory.

Events.html: 1856 – First Battle of Seattle. Marines from the USS Decatur drive off American Indian attackers after all day battle with settlers.

Events.html: 1861 – American Civil War: The state of Louisiana secedes from the Union.
Events.text: American Civil War: The state of Louisiana secedes from the Union.

Events.html: 1863 – American Civil War: General Ambrose Burnside is relieved of command of the Army of the Potomac after the disastrous Fredericksburg campaign. He is replaced by Joseph Hooker.

Events.html: 1863 – American Civil War: Governor of Massachusetts John Albion Andrew receives permission from the Secretary of War to raise a militia organization for men of African descent.

Events.html: 1870 – American Civil War: Virginia rejoins the Union.
Events.text: American Civil War: Virginia rejoins the Union.

Events.html: 1885 – Troops loyal to The Mahdi conquer Khartoum, killing the Governor-General Charles George Gordon.
Events.text: Troops loyal to The Mahdi conquer Khartoum, killing the Governor-General Charles George Gordon.

Events.html: 1905 – The world's largest diamond ever, the Cullinan weighing 3,106.75 carats (0.621350 kg), is found at the Premier Mine near Pretoria in South Africa.
Events.text: The world's largest diamond ever, the Cullinan weighing 3,106.75 carats (0.621350 kg), is found at the Premier Mine near Pretoria in South Africa.

Events.html: 1907 – The Short Magazine Lee-Enfield Mk III is officially introduced into British Military Service, and remains the second oldest military rifle still in official use.

Events.html: 1911 – Glenn H. Curtiss flies the first successful American seaplane.

Events.html: 1911 – Richard Strauss' opera Der Rosenkavalier receives its debut performance at the Dresden State Opera.

Events.html: 1915 – The Rocky Mountain National Park is established by an act of the U.S. Congress.
